\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.15}{\ignorespaces Resource utilisation of \texttt {dequantize} synthesised at $S = 8$ on the ZCU102. The core-only column excludes the AXI master adapter.}}{35}{table.caption.152}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.16}{\ignorespaces Latency breakdown of \texttt {dequantize} ($S = 8$, $GS = 4$) at \SI {150}{\mega \hertz }. Total function latency is 45 cycles (\SI {300}{\nano \second }).}}{35}{table.caption.153}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.17}{\ignorespaces C-simulation output for \texttt {matmul} with quantised input $\hat {\mathbf {x}} = [17, -41, 127, -10, 59, -127, 28, -79]$ (group scales $s_0 = 0.029134$, $s_1 = 0.035433$) and an $8 \times 8$ scaled identity weight matrix. All eight output elements match the software reference within tolerance.}}{39}{table.caption.178}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.18}{\ignorespaces Timing summary for \texttt {matmul\_top} at the \SI {150}{\mega \hertz } (\SI {6.667}{\nano \second }) target clock.}}{39}{table.caption.180}%
